HEADWORD: Siphonobranchiate
<hw>Si`pho*no*bran"chi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a siphon, or siphons, to convey water to
the gills; belonging or pertaining to the Siphonobranchiata.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the Siphonobranchiata.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

